Bring a large #pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Finely chop the @parsley{1%bunch}(chopped). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve, peel and finely chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Halve the @baby carrots{4%ounce}(halved lengthwise). Halve the @grape tomatoes{1%bunch}(halved). Cut the @zucchini{1}(cut into 1/4-inch half-moons) in half lengthwise and slice into 1/4-inch half-moons. Core, seed, and remove the white veins from the @red bell pepper{1}(cored and thinly sliced) and then thinly slice. Cut the @lemon{1}(cut into wedges) into wedges.

Heat @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #non stick pan{} over medium heat. When hot, sear the @sweet Italian pork sausage{8%ounce} for about ~{6%minutes}, turning them until evenly brown. Remove from the pan and slice into 1/2-inch rounds on a diagonal. Return the sausage to the pan and brown the slices for about ~{1-2%minutes}. Set aside.

In the same pan, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} over medium heat. Add the onion, carrot, and zucchini and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, tossing, for about ~{4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @orzo pasta{6%ounce} to the boiling water. Cook for about ~{7-9%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of pasta water, and set aside.

> Tip: Before you drain all that pasta water, reserve some for finishing your dishes. While the pasta cooks, it releases starches into the water that'll help add some body to your sauces.

While the pasta cooks, add the peppers and garlic to the pan and cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until veggies are crisp-tender. Add the tomatoes and season with salt and pepper. Cook for about ~{2%minutes}, until tomatoes are softened.

Add the sausage back to the pan with the veggies. Add the orzo, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a splash of pasta water. Toss, taste and season with salt and pepper.